Topics:
-----
1) Virtulaization Technolgy
This enables IT organizations to run more than one virtual system – 
and multiple operating systems and applications – on a single server.
  typ1-Bare Metal
  ===============
  The Type 1 hypervisor doesn't have to load an underlying OS. With direct access to the underlying hardware and
  no other software -- such as OSes and device

  type2-Hosted 
  ============
  A Type 2 hypervisor is typically installed on top of an existing OS. It is sometimes called a hosted hypervisor because it relies on the host machine's 
  preexisting OS to manage calls to CPU, memory, storage and network resources.

2) About Cloud Computing:
======================
 Cloud computing is a process to allow on-demand network access to shared computing resources.

on-demand: you use it when you need it 
n/w access :internet
shared computing resources: Memory, Storage...

Cloud computing is shared and access the data over internet.
=====================================================================
3) Types of Clouds
=====================
a) public cloud: AWS, Azure,GCP & Alibaba
b) private cloud: with in organization   ex: sbi --meghadoot
c) Hybrid cloud: Hybrid cloud is IT infrastructure that connects at least one public cloud and at least one private cloud.

3) Types of Service Models
===============================
IAAS: aws
PAAS: Elastic Beanstalk
SAAS: Example. Amazon lightsail, Google’s G Suite
	

shared-responsibility-model
===========================
Link: https://aws.amazon.com/compliance/shared-responsibility-model/

AWS Global Infrastructure:
===========================
Region, Availability Zone & Edge locations

Link: https://aws.amazon.com/about-aws/global-infrastructure/
What is a Region
geographical location ex: Mumbai

Availability Zone- data centres which contains physcial resources 

Edge locations are AWS data centers designed to deliver services with the lowest latency possible.

